+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_018Hc4Y1Kgka332QBPt6Hy6j","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here is the complete codebase analysis.\n\n---\n\n## Full Directory Structure\n\n```\n/workspace/\nâ”śâ”€â”€ .eslintrc.cjs\nâ”śâ”€â”€ .gitignore\nâ”śâ”€â”€ TASK.md\nâ”śâ”€â”€ package.json\nâ”śâ”€â”€ package-lock.json\nâ”śâ”€â”€ tsconfig.json\nâ”śâ”€â”€ vitest.config.ts\nâ”śâ”€â”€ src/\nâ”‚   â”śâ”€â”€ core/\nâ”‚   â”‚   â”śâ”€â”€ engine.ts\nâ”‚   â”‚   â”śâ”€â”€ index.ts\nâ”‚   â”‚   â”śâ”€â”€ templates.ts\nâ”‚   â”‚   â””â”€â”€ types.ts\nâ”‚   â””â”€â”€ plugins/\nâ”‚       â””â”€â”€ .gitkeep          (empty -- plugins need to be created here)\nâ””â”€â”€ tests/\n    â”śâ”€â”€ core.test.ts\n    â””â”€â”€ plugins/\n        â”śâ”€â”€ asset-pipeline.test.ts\n        â”śâ”€â”€ dev-server.test.ts\n        â”śâ”€â”€ markdown-ext.test.ts\n        â”śâ”€â”€ rss-feed.test.ts\n        â”śâ”€â”€ search-index.test.ts\n        â”śâ”€â”€ sitemap.test.ts\n        â”śâ”€â”€ syntax-highlight.test.ts\n        â””â”€â”€ taxonomy.test.ts\n```\n\n---\n\n## 1. `/workspace/package.json`\n\n- **Name:** `bench-ssg-toolkit`\n- **Type:** ES modules (`\"type\": \"module\"`)\n- **Scripts:**\n  - `build`: `tsc`\n  - `lint`: `eslint src/ tests/`\n  - `test`: `vitest run`\n- **Dependencies:**\n  - `@types/express` ^5.0.6\n  - `@types/marked` ^5.0.2\n  - `express` ^5.2.1\n  - `marked` ^17.0.2\n- **Dev Dependencies:**\n  - `@typescript-eslint/eslint-plugin` ^7.18.0\n  - `@typescript-eslint/parser` ^7.18.0\n  - `eslint` ^8.57.1\n  - `typescript` ^5.9.3\n  - `vitest` ^2.1.9\n\n---\n\n## 2. `/workspace/tsconfig.json`\n\n```json\n{\n  \"compilerOptions\": {\n    \"strict\": true,\n    \"target\": \"ES2022\",\n    \"module\": \"Node16\",\n    \"moduleResolution\": \"Node16\",\n    \"outDir\": \"./dist\",\n    \"rootDir\": \"./src\",\n    \"declaration\": true,\n    \"esModuleInterop\": true,\n    \"skipLibCheck\": true\n  },\n  \"include\": [\"src/**/*\"]\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3. Core Source Files (`/workspace/src/core/`)\n\n### 3a. `/workspace/src/core/types.ts` -- The Plugin Interface\n\nThis is the central type system. Key interfaces:\n\n```typescript\nexport interface SiteConfig {\n  title: string;\n  baseUrl: string;\n  outputDir: string;\n  contentDir: string;\n  templateDir: string;\n}\n\nexport interface ContentFile {\n  slug: string;\n  title: string;\n  content: string;        // raw content (markdown or html)\n  metadata: Record<string, unknown>;\n  date?: string;\n  tags?: string[];\n  template?: string;\n}\n\nexport interface BuildContext {\n  config: SiteConfig;\n  files: ContentFile[];\n  output: Map<string, string>;  // output path -> rendered content\n  assets: Map<string, Buffer>;  // output path -> binary data\n  data: Map<string, unknown>;   // shared plugin data store\n}\n\nexport interface PluginHooks {\n  beforeBuild?: (ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<void> | void;\n  transformContent?: (file: ContentFile, ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<ContentFile> | ContentFile;\n  afterBuild?: (ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<void> | void;\n}\n\nexport interface Plugin {\n  name: string;\n  version: string;\n  dependencies: string[];  // names of plugins this depends on\n  hooks: PluginHooks;\n}\n\nexport interface Template {\n  name: string;\n  render: (content: string, data: Record<string, unknown>) => string;\n}\n```\n\n### 3b. `/workspace/src/core/engine.ts` -- The BuildEngine\n\nThe `BuildEngine` class:\n- **`registerPlugin(plugin)`** -- adds a plugin to the internal list\n- **`registerTemplate(template)`** -- registers a named template\n- **`resolvePluginOrder()`** -- topological sort of plugins by dependencies (detects circular deps and missing deps)\n- **`build(files)`** -- the main pipeline:\n  1. Runs `beforeBuild` hooks in dependency order\n  2. Runs `transformContent` hooks on each file in plugin order\n  3. Renders templates (uses file's `template` field or `'default'`)\n  4. Runs `afterBuild` hooks in dependency order\n  5. Returns the `BuildContext`\n- **`getPlugins()`** / **`getTemplates()`** -- accessors\n\n### 3c. `/workspace/src/core/templates.ts`\n\nTwo factory functions:\n- **`createDefaultTemplate()`** -- wraps content in `<article>` with `<h1>`, optional `<time>`, and `<div class=\"content\">`\n- **`createListTemplate()`** -- wraps content in `<h1>` and `<div class=\"list\">`\n\n### 3d. `/workspace/src/core/index.ts` -- Barrel export\n\n```typescript\nexport { BuildEngine } from './engine.js';\nexport { createDefaultTemplate, createListTemplate } from './templates.js';\nexport type { BuildContext, ContentFile, Plugin, PluginHooks, SiteConfig, Template } from './types.js';\n```\n\n---\n\n## 4. `/workspace/src/plugins/` -- Currently Empty\n\nContains only `.gitkeep`. All 8 plugins need to be created here.\n\n---\n\n## 5. `/workspace/tests/core.test.ts` -- 15 Existing Tests\n\nTests the `BuildEngine`: plugin registration, template registration, build with default/list templates, raw content fallback, `beforeBuild`/`transformContent`/`afterBuild` hooks, dependency ordering, circular dependency detection, missing dependency detection, multiple plugin transform ordering, shared data store, file metadata preservation, and empty file list handling.\n\n---\n\n## 6. All 8 Plugin Test Files (Complete Content)\n\n### 6a. `/workspace/tests/plugins/markdown-ext.test.ts` (8 tests)\n\nImports `createMarkdownExtPlugin` from `../../src/plugins/markdown-ext.js`.\n\n| Test | What It Checks |\n|------|---------------|\n| converts basic markdown to HTML | `# Hello` becomes `<h1>`, `**bold**` becomes `<strong>bold</strong>` |\n| handles footnotes with `[^1]` syntax | `[^1]` becomes `<sup><a href=\"#fn-1\">1</a></sup>` |\n| renders footnote section at bottom | `<section class=\"footnotes\">` with `<li id=\"fn-1\">First note.</li>` |\n| converts `:::note` to admonition div | `<div class=\"admonition admonition-note\">` |\n| converts `:::warning` to admonition div | `<div class=\"admonition admonition-warning\">` |\n| converts `:::tip` to admonition div | `<div class=\"admonition admonition-tip\">` |\n| preserves existing HTML | `<div class=\"custom\">Already HTML</div>` passes through |\n| handles empty content | Returns defined content |\n\n### 6b. `/workspace/tests/plugins/asset-pipeline.test.ts` (8 tests)\n\nImports `createAssetPipelinePlugin` from `../../src/plugins/asset-pipeline.js`.\n\n| Test | What It Checks |\n|------|---------------|\n| rewrites relative image URLs | `src=\"./image.png\"` becomes `src=\"/assets/image.png\"` |\n| rewrites relative link URLs | `href=\"./doc.pdf\"` becomes `href=\"/assets/doc.pdf\"` |\n| leaves absolute URLs unchanged | `https://cdn.example.com/image.png` untouched |\n| generates asset manifest in ctx.data | `ctx.data.get('asset-manifest')` has `{ assets: ['photo.jpg'] }` |\n| handles files with no asset references | Content unchanged, no errors |\n| handles multiple assets in one file | All assets (`a.png`, `b.jpg`, `c.pdf`) in manifest |\n| accumulates across files | `one.png` and `two.png` from different files both in manifest |\n| does not double-process already-rewritten URLs | `/assets/image.png` stays as-is, no manifest entry |\n\n### 6c. `/workspace/tests/plugins/syntax-highlight.test.ts` (8 tests)\n\nImports `createSyntaxHighlightPlugin` from `../../src/plugins/syntax-highlight.js`.\n\n| Test | What It Checks |\n|------|---------------|\n| adds language class | `class=\"language-javascript\"` becomes `class=\"language-javascript highlighted\"` |\n| adds data-language attribute | `<pre>` gets `data-language=\"python\"` |\n| handles multiple code blocks | Both `data-language=\"js\"` and `data-language=\"py\"` present |\n| code block with no language | `<pre><code>plain code</code></pre>` is unchanged |\n| adds highlighted class | `highlighted` class present on language-tagged blocks |\n| preserves code block content | `const x: number = 42;` still present |\n| handles empty code blocks | Empty `language-js` block still gets `data-language` and `highlighted` |\n| does not modify inline code | `<code>console.log()</code>` (not inside `<pre>`) is unchanged |\n\n### 6d. `/workspace/tests/plugins/taxonomy.test.ts` (8 tests)\n\nImports `createTaxonomyPlugin` from `../../src/plugins/taxonomy.js`.\n\n| Test | What It Checks |\n|------|---------------|\n| builds tag index from file tags | `ctx.data.get('taxonomy-tags')` is a `Map<string, ContentFile[]>` |\n| generates tag listing pages | `ctx.output.has('tags/javascript.html')` containing post title |\n| handles files with no tags | Tag map size is 0 |\n| handles files with multiple tags | 3 tags = 3 entries in map |\n| tag pages list all files with that tag | Both \"First Post\" and \"Second Post\" appear on `tags/tech.html` |\n| stores tag map in ctx.data | `ctx.data.has('taxonomy-tags')` is true |\n| handles empty file list | Works without error, tag map size 0 |\n| tags are case-normalized to lowercase | `'JavaScript'` and `'JAVASCRIPT'` both normalize to `'javascript'` |\n\nUses **`beforeBuild`** to build the tag index, and **`afterBuild`** to generate tag pages.\n\n### 6e. `/workspace/tests/plugins/rss-feed.test.ts` (7 tests)\n\nImports `createRssFeedPlugin` from `../../src/plugins/rss-feed.js`.\nDependencies: `markdown-ext`, `taxonomy`.\n\n| Test | What It Checks |\n|------|---------------|\n| generates valid RSS 2.0 XML | `<?xml version=\"1.0\"`, `<rss version=\"2.0\">`, `<channel>`, `<item>` |\n| feed items contain HTML content not raw markdown | `<![CDATA[<p>This is <strong>HTML</strong> content</p>]]>` |\n| feed items include category tags from taxonomy | `<category>javascript</category>` when taxonomy-tags data present |\n| feed includes channel title | `<title>Test Site</title>` from config |\n| feed items sorted by date newest first | New > Mid > Old ordering |\n| handles files without dates | No `<pubDate>undefined</pubDate>` |\n| feed link uses baseUrl | `<link>https://example.com</link>` and per-item links |\n\nUses **`afterBuild`** to generate `feed.xml`.\n\n### 6f. `/workspace/tests/plugins/search-index.test.ts` (7 tests)\n\nImports `createSearchIndexPlugin` from `../../src/plugins/search-index.js`.\nDependencies: `markdown-ext`, `syntax-highlight`.\n\n| Test | What It Checks |\n|------|---------------|\n| generates search-index.json | `ctx.output.has('search-index.json')` |\n| index entries have title, slug, plain text | HTML stripped, plain text `'Some text here'` |\n| HTML tags stripped from indexed content | No `<` or `>` in content |\n| code blocks included in searchable text | `'const x = 1;'` present |\n| handles empty file list | Returns `[]` |\n| search index is valid JSON | Parses as array of length 2 |\n| index entries include tags if present | `tags: ['js', 'web']` in entry |\n\nUses **`afterBuild`** to generate `search-index.json`.\n\n### 6g. `/workspace/tests/plugins/sitemap.test.ts` (7 tests)\n\nImports `createSitemapPlugin` from `../../src/plugins/sitemap.js`.\nDependencies: `taxonomy`, `rss-feed`.\n\n| Test | What It Checks |\n|------|---------------|\n| generates sitemap.xml | `ctx.output.has('sitemap.xml')` |\n| includes all content page URLs | Both `post-1.html` and `post-2.html` URLs |\n| includes taxonomy tag page URLs | `tags/javascript.html` URL |\n| includes feed.xml URL | `feed.xml` in sitemap |\n| URLs use baseUrl | `https://example.com/about.html` |\n| valid XML structure | `<?xml`, `<urlset`, `</urlset>`, `<url>`, `<loc>` |\n| handles site with no tag pages | No `/tags/` in output |\n\nUses **`afterBuild`** to generate `sitemap.xml`.\n\n### 6h. `/workspace/tests/plugins/dev-server.test.ts` (7 tests)\n\nImports `createDevServerPlugin` from `../../src/plugins/dev-server.js`.\nDependencies: `asset-pipeline`, `search-index`.\n\nExpects a `DevServerConfig` structure:\n```typescript\ninterface DevServerConfig {\n  port: number;\n  routes: Array<{ path: string; handler: string }>;\n  assetPaths: string[];\n  searchIndexPath: string;\n}\n```\n\n| Test | What It Checks |\n|------|---------------|\n| stores dev-server-config in ctx.data | `ctx.data.has('dev-server-config')` |\n| config includes port setting | `typeof config.port === 'number'` |\n| config includes asset routes from asset-pipeline | Reads `asset-manifest` data, populates `assetPaths` and routes with `handler: 'asset'` |\n| config includes search index path | `/search-index.json` when output has `search-index.json` |\n| config includes content routes | Routes with `handler: 'static'` for each `.html` output |\n| default port is 3000 | `config.port === 3000` |\n| handles missing asset-pipeline data | `assetPaths` defaults to `[]` |\n\nUses **`afterBuild`** to generate the dev server config and store in `ctx.data`.\n\n---\n\n## 7. Plugin Dependency Graph (from TASK.md)\n\n```\nWave 1 (no dependencies):\n  1. markdown-ext         dependencies: []\n  2. asset-pipeline       dependencies: []\n  3. syntax-highlight     dependencies: []\n  4. taxonomy             dependencies: []\n\nWave 2 (depend on Wave 1):\n  5. rss-feed             dependencies: ['markdown-ext', 'taxonomy']\n  6. search-index         dependencies: ['markdown-ext', 'syntax-highlight']\n\nWave 3 (depend on Wave 2):\n  7. sitemap              dependencies: ['taxonomy', 'rss-feed']\n  8. dev-server           dependencies: ['asset-pipeline', 'search-index']\n```\n\n---\n\n## 8. Key Implementation Notes from the Tests\n\n1. **Each plugin exports a factory function** named `createXxxPlugin()` (e.g., `createMarkdownExtPlugin()`) that returns a `Plugin` object.\n\n2. **Plugin hooks used per plugin:**\n   - `markdown-ext`: `transformContent`\n   - `asset-pipeline`: `transformContent` (rewrites URLs, builds manifest in `ctx.data`)\n   - `syntax-highlight`: `transformContent`\n   - `taxonomy`: `beforeBuild` (builds tag index) + `afterBuild` (generates tag pages)\n   - `rss-feed`: `afterBuild` (generates `feed.xml`)\n   - `search-index`: `afterBuild` (generates `search-index.json`)\n   - `sitemap`: `afterBuild` (generates `sitemap.xml`)\n   - `dev-server`: `afterBuild` (stores config in `ctx.data`)\n\n3. **Shared data keys in `ctx.data`:**\n   - `'taxonomy-tags'` -- `Map<string, ContentFile[]>` (set by taxonomy, read by rss-feed)\n   - `'asset-manifest'` -- `{ assets: string[] }` (set by asset-pipeline, read by dev-server)\n   - `'dev-server-config'` -- `DevServerConfig` object (set by dev-server)\n\n4. **Shared output keys in `ctx.output`:**\n   - `'feed.xml'` -- RSS feed (set by rss-feed, detected by sitemap)\n   - `'search-index.json'` -- search index JSON (set by search-index, detected by dev-server)\n   - `'sitemap.xml'` -- sitemap XML (set by sitemap)\n   - `'tags/<tagname>.html'` -- tag pages (set by taxonomy)\n\n5. **`marked`** is available as a dependency (version ^17.0.2) for the markdown-ext plugin to use for Markdown-to-HTML conversion. Footnotes and admonition containers need custom pre/post-processing around `marked`.\n\n6. **`express`** is available but none of the test files actually start a server -- `dev-server` just generates a config object."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: acd3af4 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 36274\ntool_uses: 22\nduration_ms: 87280</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f8feecf4-a0c5-4c57-9f40-722e41d8ebb2","uuid":"48f6f586-7add-4db4-a5dc-64d1058eb4b8","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the entire codebase structure. I need to understand:\n1. The full directory structure\n2. The Plugin interface in src/core/types.ts\n3. All files in src/core/\n4. All test files in tests/ (especially tests/plugins/*.test.ts)\n5. The package.json for dependencies and scripts\n6. The tsconfig.json\n7. Any existing files in src/plugins/\n\nRead ALL of these files completely - every test file in tests/plugins/ is critical. I need the COMPLETE content of every file.","agentId":"acd3af4","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here is the complete codebase analysis.\n\n---\n\n## Full Directory Structure\n\n```\n/workspace/\nâ”śâ”€â”€ .eslintrc.cjs\nâ”śâ”€â”€ .gitignore\nâ”śâ”€â”€ TASK.md\nâ”śâ”€â”€ package.json\nâ”śâ”€â”€ package-lock.json\nâ”śâ”€â”€ tsconfig.json\nâ”śâ”€â”€ vitest.config.ts\nâ”śâ”€â”€ src/\nâ”‚   â”śâ”€â”€ core/\nâ”‚   â”‚   â”śâ”€â”€ engine.ts\nâ”‚   â”‚   â”śâ”€â”€ index.ts\nâ”‚   â”‚   â”śâ”€â”€ templates.ts\nâ”‚   â”‚   â””â”€â”€ types.ts\nâ”‚   â””â”€â”€ plugins/\nâ”‚       â””â”€â”€ .gitkeep          (empty -- plugins need to be created here)\nâ””â”€â”€ tests/\n    â”śâ”€â”€ core.test.ts\n    â””â”€â”€ plugins/\n        â”śâ”€â”€ asset-pipeline.test.ts\n        â”śâ”€â”€ dev-server.test.ts\n        â”śâ”€â”€ markdown-ext.test.ts\n        â”śâ”€â”€ rss-feed.test.ts\n        â”śâ”€â”€ search-index.test.ts\n        â”śâ”€â”€ sitemap.test.ts\n        â”śâ”€â”€ syntax-highlight.test.ts\n        â””â”€â”€ taxonomy.test.ts\n```\n\n---\n\n## 1. `/workspace/package.json`\n\n- **Name:** `bench-ssg-toolkit`\n- **Type:** ES modules (`\"type\": \"module\"`)\n- **Scripts:**\n  - `build`: `tsc`\n  - `lint`: `eslint src/ tests/`\n  - `test`: `vitest run`\n- **Dependencies:**\n  - `@types/express` ^5.0.6\n  - `@types/marked` ^5.0.2\n  - `express` ^5.2.1\n  - `marked` ^17.0.2\n- **Dev Dependencies:**\n  - `@typescript-eslint/eslint-plugin` ^7.18.0\n  - `@typescript-eslint/parser` ^7.18.0\n  - `eslint` ^8.57.1\n  - `typescript` ^5.9.3\n  - `vitest` ^2.1.9\n\n---\n\n## 2. `/workspace/tsconfig.json`\n\n```json\n{\n  \"compilerOptions\": {\n    \"strict\": true,\n    \"target\": \"ES2022\",\n    \"module\": \"Node16\",\n    \"moduleResolution\": \"Node16\",\n    \"outDir\": \"./dist\",\n    \"rootDir\": \"./src\",\n    \"declaration\": true,\n    \"esModuleInterop\": true,\n    \"skipLibCheck\": true\n  },\n  \"include\": [\"src/**/*\"]\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3. Core Source Files (`/workspace/src/core/`)\n\n### 3a. `/workspace/src/core/types.ts` -- The Plugin Interface\n\nThis is the central type system. Key interfaces:\n\n```typescript\nexport interface SiteConfig {\n  title: string;\n  baseUrl: string;\n  outputDir: string;\n  contentDir: string;\n  templateDir: string;\n}\n\nexport interface ContentFile {\n  slug: string;\n  title: string;\n  content: string;        // raw content (markdown or html)\n  metadata: Record<string, unknown>;\n  date?: string;\n  tags?: string[];\n  template?: string;\n}\n\nexport interface BuildContext {\n  config: SiteConfig;\n  files: ContentFile[];\n  output: Map<string, string>;  // output path -> rendered content\n  assets: Map<string, Buffer>;  // output path -> binary data\n  data: Map<string, unknown>;   // shared plugin data store\n}\n\nexport interface PluginHooks {\n  beforeBuild?: (ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<void> | void;\n  transformContent?: (file: ContentFile, ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<ContentFile> | ContentFile;\n  afterBuild?: (ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<void> | void;\n}\n\nexport interface Plugin {\n  name: string;\n  version: string;\n  dependencies: string[];  // names of plugins this depends on\n  hooks: PluginHooks;\n}\n\nexport interface Template {\n  name: string;\n  render: (content: string, data: Record<string, unknown>) => string;\n}\n```\n\n### 3b. `/workspace/src/core/engine.ts` -- The BuildEngine\n\nThe `BuildEngine` class:\n- **`registerPlugin(plugin)`** -- adds a plugin to the internal list\n- **`registerTemplate(template)`** -- registers a named template\n- **`resolvePluginOrder()`** -- topological sort of plugins by dependencies (detects circular deps and missing deps)\n- **`build(files)`** -- the main pipeline:\n  1. Runs `beforeBuild` hooks in dependency order\n  2. Runs `transformContent` hooks on each file in plugin order\n  3. Renders templates (uses file's `template` field or `'default'`)\n  4. Runs `afterBuild` hooks in dependency order\n  5. Returns the `BuildContext`\n- **`getPlugins()`** / **`getTemplates()`** -- accessors\n\n### 3c. `/workspace/src/core/templates.ts`\n\nTwo factory functions:\n- **`createDefaultTemplate()`** -- wraps content in `<article>` with `<h1>`, optional `<time>`, and `<div class=\"content\">`\n- **`createListTemplate()`** -- wraps content in `<h1>` and `<div class=\"list\">`\n\n### 3d. `/workspace/src/core/index.ts` -- Barrel export\n\n```typescript\nexport { BuildEngine } from './engine.js';\nexport { createDefaultTemplate, createListTemplate } from './templates.js';\nexport type { BuildContext, ContentFile, Plugin, PluginHooks, SiteConfig, Template } from './types.js';\n```\n\n---\n\n## 4. `/workspace/src/plugins/` -- Currently Empty\n\nContains only `.gitkeep`. All 8 plugins need to be created here.\n\n---\n\n## 5. `/workspace/tests/core.test.ts` -- 15 Existing Tests\n\nTests the `BuildEngine`: plugin registration, template registration, build with default/list templates, raw content fallback, `beforeBuild`/`transformContent`/`afterBuild` hooks, dependency ordering, circular dependency detection, missing dependency detection, multiple plugin transform ordering, shared data store, file metadata preservation, and empty file list handling.\n\n---\n\n## 6. All 8 Plugin Test Files (Complete Content)\n\n### 6a. `/workspace/tests/plugins/markdown-ext.test.ts` (8 tests)\n\nImports `createMarkdownExtPlugin` from `../../src/plugins/markdown-ext.js`.\n\n| Test | What It Checks |\n|------|---------------|\n| converts basic markdown to HTML | `# Hello` becomes `<h1>`, `**bold**` becomes `<strong>bold</strong>` |\n| handles footnotes with `[^1]` syntax | `[^1]` becomes `<sup><a href=\"#fn-1\">1</a></sup>` |\n| renders footnote section at bottom | `<section class=\"footnotes\">` with `<li id=\"fn-1\">First note.</li>` |\n| converts `:::note` to admonition div | `<div class=\"admonition admonition-note\">` |\n| converts `:::warning` to admonition div | `<div class=\"admonition admonition-warning\">` |\n| converts `:::tip` to admonition div | `<div class=\"admonition admonition-tip\">` |\n| preserves existing HTML | `<div class=\"custom\">Already HTML</div>` passes through |\n| handles empty content | Returns defined content |\n\n### 6b. `/workspace/tests/plugins/asset-pipeline.test.ts` (8 tests)\n\nImports `createAssetPipelinePlugin` from `../../src/plugins/asset-pipeline.js`.\n\n| Test | What It Checks |\n|------|---------------|\n| rewrites relative image URLs | `src=\"./image.png\"` becomes `src=\"/assets/image.png\"` |\n| rewrites relative link URLs | `href=\"./doc.pdf\"` becomes `href=\"/assets/doc.pdf\"` |\n| leaves absolute URLs unchanged | `https://cdn.example.com/image.png` untouched |\n| generates asset manifest in ctx.data | `ctx.data.get('asset-manifest')` has `{ assets: ['photo.jpg'] }` |\n| handles files with no asset references | Content unchanged, no errors |\n| handles multiple assets in one file | All assets (`a.png`, `b.jpg`, `c.pdf`) in manifest |\n| accumulates across files | `one.png` and `two.png` from different files both in manifest |\n| does not double-process already-rewritten URLs | `/assets/image.png` stays as-is, no manifest entry |\n\n### 6c. `/workspace/tests/plugins/syntax-highlight.test.ts` (8 tests)\n\nImports `createSyntaxHighlightPlugin` from `../../src/plugins/syntax-highlight.js`.\n\n| Test | What It Checks |\n|------|---------------|\n| adds language class | `class=\"language-javascript\"` becomes `class=\"language-javascript highlighted\"` |\n| adds data-language attribute | `<pre>` gets `data-language=\"python\"` |\n| handles multiple code blocks | Both `data-language=\"js\"` and `data-language=\"py\"` present |\n| code block with no language | `<pre><code>plain code</code></pre>` is unchanged |\n| adds highlighted class | `highlighted` class present on language-tagged blocks |\n| preserves code block content | `const x: number = 42;` still present |\n| handles empty code blocks | Empty `language-js` block still gets `data-language` and `highlighted` |\n| does not modify inline code | `<code>console.log()</code>` (not inside `<pre>`) is unchanged |\n\n### 6d. `/workspace/tests/plugins/taxonomy.test.ts` (8 tests)\n\nImports `createTaxonomyPlugin` from `../../src/plugins/taxonomy.js`.\n\n| Test | What It Checks |\n|------|---------------|\n| builds tag index from file tags | `ctx.data.get('taxonomy-tags')` is a `Map<string, ContentFile[]>` |\n| generates tag listing pages | `ctx.output.has('tags/javascript.html')` containing post title |\n| handles files with no tags | Tag map size is 0 |\n| handles files with multiple tags | 3 tags = 3 entries in map |\n| tag pages list all files with that tag | Both \"First Post\" and \"Second Post\" appear on `tags/tech.html` |\n| stores tag map in ctx.data | `ctx.data.has('taxonomy-tags')` is true |\n| handles empty file list | Works without error, tag map size 0 |\n| tags are case-normalized to lowercase | `'JavaScript'` and `'JAVASCRIPT'` both normalize to `'javascript'` |\n\nUses **`beforeBuild`** to build the tag index, and **`afterBuild`** to generate tag pages.\n\n### 6e. `/workspace/tests/plugins/rss-feed.test.ts` (7 tests)\n\nImports `createRssFeedPlugin` from `../../src/plugins/rss-feed.js`.\nDependencies: `markdown-ext`, `taxonomy`.\n\n| Test | What It Checks |\n|------|---------------|\n| generates valid RSS 2.0 XML | `<?xml version=\"1.0\"`, `<rss version=\"2.0\">`, `<channel>`, `<item>` |\n| feed items contain HTML content not raw markdown | `<![CDATA[<p>This is <strong>HTML</strong> content</p>]]>` |\n| feed items include category tags from taxonomy | `<category>javascript</category>` when taxonomy-tags data present |\n| feed includes channel title | `<title>Test Site</title>` from config |\n| feed items sorted by date newest first | New > Mid > Old ordering |\n| handles files without dates | No `<pubDate>undefined</pubDate>` |\n| feed link uses baseUrl | `<link>https://example.com</link>` and per-item links |\n\nUses **`afterBuild`** to generate `feed.xml`.\n\n### 6f. `/workspace/tests/plugins/search-index.test.ts` (7 tests)\n\nImports `createSearchIndexPlugin` from `../../src/plugins/search-index.js`.\nDependencies: `markdown-ext`, `syntax-highlight`.\n\n| Test | What It Checks |\n|------|---------------|\n| generates search-index.json | `ctx.output.has('search-index.json')` |\n| index entries have title, slug, plain text | HTML stripped, plain text `'Some text here'` |\n| HTML tags stripped from indexed content | No `<` or `>` in content |\n| code blocks included in searchable text | `'const x = 1;'` present |\n| handles empty file list | Returns `[]` |\n| search index is valid JSON | Parses as array of length 2 |\n| index entries include tags if present | `tags: ['js', 'web']` in entry |\n\nUses **`afterBuild`** to generate `search-index.json`.\n\n### 6g. `/workspace/tests/plugins/sitemap.test.ts` (7 tests)\n\nImports `createSitemapPlugin` from `../../src/plugins/sitemap.js`.\nDependencies: `taxonomy`, `rss-feed`.\n\n| Test | What It Checks |\n|------|---------------|\n| generates sitemap.xml | `ctx.output.has('sitemap.xml')` |\n| includes all content page URLs | Both `post-1.html` and `post-2.html` URLs |\n| includes taxonomy tag page URLs | `tags/javascript.html` URL |\n| includes feed.xml URL | `feed.xml` in sitemap |\n| URLs use baseUrl | `https://example.com/about.html` |\n| valid XML structure | `<?xml`, `<urlset`, `</urlset>`, `<url>`, `<loc>` |\n| handles site with no tag pages | No `/tags/` in output |\n\nUses **`afterBuild`** to generate `sitemap.xml`.\n\n### 6h. `/workspace/tests/plugins/dev-server.test.ts` (7 tests)\n\nImports `createDevServerPlugin` from `../../src/plugins/dev-server.js`.\nDependencies: `asset-pipeline`, `search-index`.\n\nExpects a `DevServerConfig` structure:\n```typescript\ninterface DevServerConfig {\n  port: number;\n  routes: Array<{ path: string; handler: string }>;\n  assetPaths: string[];\n  searchIndexPath: string;\n}\n```\n\n| Test | What It Checks |\n|------|---------------|\n| stores dev-server-config in ctx.data | `ctx.data.has('dev-server-config')` |\n| config includes port setting | `typeof config.port === 'number'` |\n| config includes asset routes from asset-pipeline | Reads `asset-manifest` data, populates `assetPaths` and routes with `handler: 'asset'` |\n| config includes search index path | `/search-index.json` when output has `search-index.json` |\n| config includes content routes | Routes with `handler: 'static'` for each `.html` output |\n| default port is 3000 | `config.port === 3000` |\n| handles missing asset-pipeline data | `assetPaths` defaults to `[]` |\n\nUses **`afterBuild`** to generate the dev server config and store in `ctx.data`.\n\n---\n\n## 7. Plugin Dependency Graph (from TASK.md)\n\n```\nWave 1 (no dependencies):\n  1. markdown-ext         dependencies: []\n  2. asset-pipeline       dependencies: []\n  3. syntax-highlight     dependencies: []\n  4. taxonomy             dependencies: []\n\nWave 2 (depend on Wave 1):\n  5. rss-feed             dependencies: ['markdown-ext', 'taxonomy']\n  6. search-index         dependencies: ['markdown-ext', 'syntax-highlight']\n\nWave 3 (depend on Wave 2):\n  7. sitemap              dependencies: ['taxonomy', 'rss-feed']\n  8. dev-server           dependencies: ['asset-pipeline', 'search-index']\n```\n\n---\n\n## 8. Key Implementation Notes from the Tests\n\n1. **Each plugin exports a factory function** named `createXxxPlugin()` (e.g., `createMarkdownExtPlugin()`) that returns a `Plugin` object.\n\n2. **Plugin hooks used per plugin:**\n   - `markdown-ext`: `transformContent`\n   - `asset-pipeline`: `transformContent` (rewrites URLs, builds manifest in `ctx.data`)\n   - `syntax-highlight`: `transformContent`\n   - `taxonomy`: `beforeBuild` (builds tag index) + `afterBuild` (generates tag pages)\n   - `rss-feed`: `afterBuild` (generates `feed.xml`)\n   - `search-index`: `afterBuild` (generates `search-index.json`)\n   - `sitemap`: `afterBuild` (generates `sitemap.xml`)\n   - `dev-server`: `afterBuild` (stores config in `ctx.data`)\n\n3. **Shared data keys in `ctx.data`:**\n   - `'taxonomy-tags'` -- `Map<string, ContentFile[]>` (set by taxonomy, read by rss-feed)\n   - `'asset-manifest'` -- `{ assets: string[] }` (set by asset-pipeline, read by dev-server)\n   - `'dev-server-config'` -- `DevServerConfig` object (set by dev-server)\n\n4. **Shared output keys in `ctx.output`:**\n   - `'feed.xml'` -- RSS feed (set by rss-feed, detected by sitemap)\n   - `'search-index.json'` -- search index JSON (set by search-index, detected by dev-server)\n   - `'sitemap.xml'` -- sitemap XML (set by sitemap)\n   - `'tags/<tagname>.html'` -- tag pages (set by taxonomy)\n\n5. **`marked`** is available as a dependency (version ^17.0.2) for the markdown-ext plugin to use for Markdown-to-HTML conversion. Footnotes and admonition containers need custom pre/post-processing around `marked`.\n\n6. **`express`** is available but none of the test files actually start a server -- `dev-server` just generates a config object."}],"totalDurationMs":87280,"totalTokens":36274,"totalToolUseCount":22,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":13043,"cache_read_input_tokens":18735,"output_tokens":4495,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":13043,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[]}}}
